TITLE: My First Childhood Divine Experience & Cosmic Snake | 1984 | P1
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BJvqrY2xdP8
DATE: March 11, 2026 (recording date); events described from 1984 onward
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
Recorded on March 11, 2026 at 10:08 PM, this is Part 1 of a personal spiritual experience series. Maa Noor Ananta describes how her spiritual awakening was triggered in 1984 when she was a young child. Even before the key event, she had begun sensing a presence walking alongside her -- whether she was going to school, playing, or alone in her room. Her attention was repeatedly drawn toward this unseen companion, though at that age she could not fully comprehend what was happening.

The pivotal childhood experience occurred one night while she was waiting in bed for her mother to finish kitchen work. A cosmic snake appeared and entered her body through her nose or mouth, going into her stomach. She was terrified and ran crying to her mother, saying a snake had gone inside her. Her mother dismissed it and put her to sleep, but the child could not sleep all night, fearing she would die. From that night onward, a "tandav" (cosmic upheaval) began in her life. She would periodically remind her mother about the snake, but was always ignored. The fear intensified every evening -- she dreaded nightfall because strange sensations would occur in her body as she fell asleep. She would try to stay awake all night to avoid these experiences.

During this same period (1984), two major national events drew her attention in unexplainable ways: the Bhopal Gas Tragedy, where her focus was mysteriously pulled toward the one child who survived; and the assassination of Indira Gandhi, which she witnessed emotionally through her father's tears while listening to radio news during school lunch break. She had no understanding of politics or these events, yet her consciousness was being directed toward them repeatedly. Real snakes also began appearing in her house, visible only to her.

From 1984 onward, her interest in studies and sports began fading. She became increasingly withdrawn, quiet, sad, stopped eating, and started spending time alone in her room. A tomboy who loved cricket, badminton, and marble games, she gradually lost interest in all activities. She became aware that something profound was happening inside her body -- she could identify specific body parts where unusual activity was occurring and began paying full attention to these internal changes. The cosmic snake experience marked the beginning of her spiritual awakening, though she had no framework to understand it at the time.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- The "cosmic snake" entering her body in 1984 was a kundalini activation event, though she only understood this much later in life
- She had premonitory awareness from early childhood -- sensing an unseen presence accompanying her constantly
- Her attention was cosmically directed toward the Bhopal Gas Tragedy survivor child and Indira Gandhi's assassination, suggesting a connection to major karmic events of India in 1984
- Real snakes would appear in her house but were visible only to her -- a physical manifestation connected to her kundalini awakening
- The cosmic snake triggered a complete "tandav" (upheaval) in her life -- loss of interest in studies, sports, social withdrawal, and mysterious bodily sensations
- She experienced the classic symptoms of spontaneous kundalini awakening: fear, body sensations, withdrawal from worldly activities, sleeplessness, and heightened awareness
- Even as a child, she was being "matured" through these experiences by a higher cosmic intelligence

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- 1984: Cosmic snake enters her body one night while waiting for her mother -- kundalini activation begins
- 1984: Bhopal Gas Tragedy occurs; her attention is mysteriously drawn to the surviving child
- 1984 (October 31): Indira Gandhi assassinated; she witnesses her father crying while listening to radio news during school lunch break
- 1984 onward: Begins losing interest in studies and sports; becomes withdrawn and silent
- 1984 onward: Real snakes start appearing in the house, visible only to her
- 1984 onward: Nightly fear and bodily sensations begin; she tries to stay awake to avoid them
- March 11, 2026: This video recorded at 10:08 PM

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "एक कॉस्मिक स्नेक आया और मेरे नाक से या मुंह से मेरे अंदर चला गया" = "A cosmic snake came and entered inside me through my nose or mouth"
- "उस दिन से मेरी जिंदगी में एक तांडव शुरू हो गया" = "From that day, a tandav (cosmic upheaval) began in my life"
- "मेरे अंदर एक सांप चला गया है, आप इस बात को मान नहीं रहे हो" = "A snake has gone inside me, you are not believing this"
- "हमारे घर में अक्सर सांप निकल आते थे और वो सांप सिर्फ मुझे ही दिखते थे" = "Snakes would often appear in our house and they were visible only to me"
- "जैसे ही शाम होने लगती है मुझे होता है कि दिन निकल गया... अब रात को कुछ तो होगा" = "As evening would come, I would feel the day is gone... now something will happen at night"
- "मेरे शरीर के अंदर कुछ होता है" = "Something happens inside my body"

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: This relates to the initial cosmic awakening and kundalini activation of a divine soul incarnated for Yug Parivartan. The 1984 timing is significant -- coinciding with major karmic events in India (Bhopal tragedy, Indira Gandhi assassination). The cosmic snake represents the activation of the primordial serpent energy (kundalini shakti) that would eventually drive the entire Yug Parivartan mission. This is the origin story of how divine consciousness began manifesting in a child who would later become the voice of the new age transition.


